item.title: [HIVE-19629] Enable Decimal64 reader after orc version upgrade
item.description: ORC 1.5.0 supports new fast decimal 64 reader. New VRB has to be created for making use of decimal 64 column vectors. Also LLAP IO will need a new reader to reader from long stream to decimal 64.
item.summary: Enable Decimal64 reader after orc version upgrade

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Found some issues wrt. mixing up orc write version (one with decimal64 and one without). Updated patch and tests.
Will post the patch in RB after ORC upgrade. Patch is up for review though. sershe can you please take a look?

The new line 403 in RecordReaderImpl does not look right.  To convert from DECIMAL_64 long to HiveDecimalWritable you should use the HiveDecimalWritable.deserialize64 method that pass the long and the scale...

result.setFromLong(((Decimal64ColumnVector) vector).vector[row]);
Thanks mmccline for catching that. Will address it in the next patch.

mmccline I am seeing in many places DecimalColumnVector is type casted without checking for instance of Decimal64ColumnVector. There are just too many places that would require changes (variant of Decimal64ColumnVector). Before doing that wanted to make sure if that is expected? Since orc reader now returns Decimal64ColumnVector I would assume all vector expressions, templates and operators has to be updated accordingly. Is that right?

No.

The Vectorizer only plans DECIMAL_64 when 2 conditions are true:

1) The input format supports DECIMAL_64 (Vectorizer.getVectorizedInputFormatSupports currently returns null.  We need to enhance it to ask the input format if it supports DECIMAL_64).  The only input format that currently supports DECIMAL_64 is TEXTFILE and in VectorPartionDesc.VECTOR_DESERIALIZE mode (i.e. it uses the Fast Vector deserialization).

2) And, the environment variable hive.vectorized.input.format.supports.enabled contains "decimal_64".  We always have an environment variable that can turn off the feature.

So, the quandary that LLAP is it wants to encode and cache as Decimal64ColumnVector but the Vectorizer is not always going to request DECIMAL_64.  So, a column cast operation will be required somewhere in the pipeline to convert from Decimal64ColumnVector to DecimalColumnVector.  The VectorizedRowBatchCtx from MapWork says what the Vectorizer wants.  I.e. rowColumnTypeInfos and rowDataTypePhysicalVariations will have DecimalTypeInfo and DataTypePhysicalVariation.DECIMAL_64.

I was not able to update all VectorExpression to handle DECIMAL_64.  The Vectorizer does a good job on the common ones like comparisions, addition/subtraction, sum.  But when it doesn't have DECIMAL_64 support for a VectorExpression combination it will toss a cast in.
The conversion class for vectorization is ConvertDecimal64ToDecimal.

Thanks Matt for the pointer. Looks like vectorizer already handles any impedance between DECIMAL_64 and DECIMAL types, which I think will make the patch relatively easier. Will upload a patch shortly.
